---
layout: layout-base.njk
layoutClass: "dataPage"
title: "U.S. Garden Climate Atlas: Frost-Free Days & Growing Degree Days | GrowByDate"
description: A visual atlas of U.S. garden climates using frost-free days and base-50°F growing degree days across the current GrowByDate city dataset.
canonical: "https://growbydate.com/data/us-garden-climate-atlas/"
---

<section class="card leaderboardHero resourceHero">
  <p class="eyebrow">Map-style climate resource</p>
  <h1>U.S. Garden Climate Atlas</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    A visual guide to frost-free days, seasonal crop heat, and growing-season pressure across U.S. cities in the GrowByDate dataset.
  </p>
  <p class="small">Updated {{ resourceUsClimateAtlas.updated }} · {{ resourceUsClimateAtlas.totalUsCities }} U.S. cities across {{ resourceUsClimateAtlas.totalUsStates }} states with both frost and GDD reference data.</p>
</section>

<section class="leaderboardStatGrid" aria-label="U.S. garden climate atlas summary">
  <article class="leaderboardStat">
    <span class="statLabel">Median frost-free season</span>
    <strong>{{ resourceUsClimateAtlas.medianFrostFreeDays }} days</strong>
    <span class="small">Median across the U.S. cities in the atlas.</span>
  </article>
  <article class="leaderboardStat">
    <span class="statLabel">Median base-50 GDD</span>
    <strong>{{ resourceUsClimateAtlas.medianGddBase50 }}</strong>
    <span class="small">Median seasonal heat accumulation across U.S. cities.</span>
  </article>
  <article class="leaderboardStat">
    <span class="statLabel">Core lesson</span>
    <strong>Time ≠ heat</strong>
    <span class="small">A longer frost-free season does not always mean a warmer crop season.</span>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="card resourceIntroGrid" aria-label="U.S. garden climate atlas takeaways">
  <article>
    <p class="eyebrow">Outdoor window</p>
    <h3>Frost-free days show how long tender crops usually have outside.</h2>
    <p>A shorter frost-free window pushes gardeners toward fast varieties, transplants, frost protection, or more conservative crop choices.</p>
  </article>
  <article>
    <p class="eyebrow">Crop heat</p>
    <h3>GDD shows how much warmth accumulates inside that window.</h2>
    <p>Warm-season crops such as tomatoes, peppers, squash, corn, okra, and melons need more than calendar time. They need usable heat.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="card resourceChartCard">
  <div class="resourceSectionHeader">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Climate point map</p>
      <h2>U.S. frost-free season by city</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="small">Points are positioned by city latitude and longitude. Larger, warmer-coloured points represent longer frost-free windows.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="atlasMapFrame" role="img" aria-label="Approximate point map of U.S. cities by frost-free season length.">
    <div class="atlasMap atlasMapFrost">
      <div class="atlasMapHeader">
        <strong>U.S. Frost-Free Season by City</strong>
        <span>Larger, warmer dots = longer frost-free season</span>
      </div>
      <div class="atlasGuideLayer" aria-hidden="true">
        {% for x in resourceUsClimateAtlas.atlasGuideLines %}
          <span class="atlasGuideLine" style="left:{{ x }}%;"></span>
        {% endfor %}
        {% for label in resourceUsClimateAtlas.atlasNorthLabels %}
          <span class="atlasNorthLabel" style="left:{{ label.x }}%;top:{{ label.y }}%;">{{ label.label }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
        {% for label in resourceUsClimateAtlas.atlasProvinceGuides %}
          <span class="atlasProvinceLabel" style="left:{{ label.x }}%;top:{{ label.y }}%;">{{ label.label }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% for row in resourceUsClimateAtlas.usCities %}
        <a class="atlasPoint frost-{{ row.frostBandClass }}" href="{{ row.cityUrl }}" style="left:{{ row.mapX }}%;top:{{ row.mapY }}%;" title="{{ row.cityName }}, {{ row.regionAbbr }}: {{ row.frostFreeDays }} frost-free days">
          <span class="sr-only">{{ row.cityName }}, {{ row.regionName }}: {{ row.frostFreeDays }} frost-free days.</span>
        </a>
      {% endfor %}
      {% for row in resourceUsClimateAtlas.mapLabelCities %}
        <a class="atlasCityLabel" href="{{ row.cityUrl }}" style="left:{{ row.mapX }}%;top:{{ row.mapY }}%;--label-x:{{ row.labelDx }}px;--label-y:{{ row.labelDy }}px;">{{ row.cityName }}</a>
      {% endfor %}
      <span class="atlasSourceLine">GrowByDate.com · U.S. Garden Climate Atlas</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="resourceLegend atlasLegend">
    {% for band in resourceUsClimateAtlas.frostBands %}
      <span class="legend-frost-{{ band.className }}"><i></i>{{ band.label }} <small>{{ band.range }}</small></span>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card resourceChartCard">
  <div class="resourceSectionHeader">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Climate point map</p>
      <h2>U.S. base-50°F GDD by city</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="small">Same city positions, different signal. Larger, warmer-coloured points represent higher seasonal heat accumulation.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="atlasMapFrame" role="img" aria-label="Approximate point map of U.S. cities by base-50 growing degree days.">
    <div class="atlasMap atlasMapGdd">
      <div class="atlasMapHeader">
        <strong>U.S. Growing Degree Days by City</strong>
        <span>Larger, warmer dots = more seasonal crop heat</span>
      </div>
      <div class="atlasGuideLayer" aria-hidden="true">
        {% for x in resourceUsClimateAtlas.atlasGuideLines %}
          <span class="atlasGuideLine" style="left:{{ x }}%;"></span>
        {% endfor %}
        {% for label in resourceUsClimateAtlas.atlasNorthLabels %}
          <span class="atlasNorthLabel" style="left:{{ label.x }}%;top:{{ label.y }}%;">{{ label.label }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
        {% for label in resourceUsClimateAtlas.atlasProvinceGuides %}
          <span class="atlasProvinceLabel" style="left:{{ label.x }}%;top:{{ label.y }}%;">{{ label.label }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% for row in resourceUsClimateAtlas.usCities %}
        <a class="atlasPoint gdd-{{ row.gddBandClass }}" href="{{ row.cityUrl }}" style="left:{{ row.mapX }}%;top:{{ row.mapY }}%;" title="{{ row.cityName }}, {{ row.regionAbbr }}: {{ row.gddBase50 }} base-50 GDD">
          <span class="sr-only">{{ row.cityName }}, {{ row.regionName }}: {{ row.gddBase50 }} base-50 GDD.</span>
        </a>
      {% endfor %}
      {% for row in resourceUsClimateAtlas.mapLabelCities %}
        <a class="atlasCityLabel" href="{{ row.cityUrl }}" style="left:{{ row.mapX }}%;top:{{ row.mapY }}%;--label-x:{{ row.labelDx }}px;--label-y:{{ row.labelDy }}px;">{{ row.cityName }}</a>
      {% endfor %}
      <span class="atlasSourceLine">GrowByDate.com · U.S. Garden Climate Atlas</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="resourceLegend atlasLegend">
    {% for band in resourceUsClimateAtlas.gddBands %}
      <span class="legend-gdd-{{ band.className }}"><i></i>{{ band.label }} <small>{{ band.range }}</small></span>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Climate leaders and pressure points</h2>
  <p>
    The fastest read is often in the extremes: which places have the most outdoor time, which places are most compressed, and which places accumulate the most usable crop heat.
  </p>
  <div class="resourceRankGrid compact">
    <article>
      <h3>Longest frost-free seasons</h3>
      <ol class="tight">
        {% for row in resourceUsClimateAtlas.longestSeasons %}
          {% if loop.index <= 5 %}<li><a href="{{ row.cityUrl }}">{{ row.cityName }}, {{ row.regionAbbr }}</a> — {{ row.frostFreeDays }} days</li>{% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Shortest frost-free seasons</h3>
      <ol class="tight">
        {% for row in resourceUsClimateAtlas.shortestSeasons %}
          {% if loop.index <= 5 %}<li><a href="{{ row.cityUrl }}">{{ row.cityName }}, {{ row.regionAbbr }}</a> — {{ row.frostFreeDays }} days</li>{% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Highest base-50 GDD</h3>
      <ol class="tight">
        {% for row in resourceUsClimateAtlas.highestGdd %}
          {% if loop.index <= 5 %}<li><a href="{{ row.cityUrl }}">{{ row.cityName }}, {{ row.regionAbbr }}</a> — {{ row.gddBase50 }} GDD</li>{% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Lowest base-50 GDD</h3>
      <ol class="tight">
        {% for row in resourceUsClimateAtlas.lowestGdd %}
          {% if loop.index <= 5 %}<li><a href="{{ row.cityUrl }}">{{ row.cityName }}, {{ row.regionAbbr }}</a> — {{ row.gddBase50 }} GDD</li>{% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card leaderboardTableWrap">
  <h2>State summary</h2>
  <p class="small">Median values are calculated from the U.S. cities currently included in the GrowByDate dataset.</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>State</th>
        <th>Cities</th>
        <th>Median frost-free days</th>
        <th>Median base-50 GDD</th>
        <th>Longest-season city</th>
        <th>Highest-GDD city</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for row in resourceUsClimateAtlas.stateSummaries %}
        <tr>
          <td><strong>{{ row.regionName }}</strong></td>
          <td>{{ row.cityCount }}</td>
          <td>{{ row.medianFrostFreeDays }}</td>
          <td>{{ row.medianGddBase50 }}</td>
          <td>{% if row.longestSeasonCity %}<a href="{{ row.longestSeasonCity.cityUrl }}">{{ row.longestSeasonCity.cityName }}</a>{% endif %}</td>
          <td>{% if row.highestGddCity %}<a href="{{ row.highestGddCity.cityUrl }}">{{ row.highestGddCity.cityName }}</a>{% endif %}</td>
        </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>How to use the atlas</h2>
  <p>
    Frost-free days estimate the outdoor window for tender crops. Base-50°F GDD estimates how much crop heat accumulates during the season. For warm-season crops, the best planning read comes from comparing both signals together.
  </p>
  <ul class="tight">
    <li>Use the frost-free map to compare outdoor season length.</li>
    <li>Use the GDD map to compare seasonal heat for crops such as tomatoes, peppers, corn, squash, okra, and melons.</li>
    <li>Use <a href="/data/long-season-vs-warm-season/">Long Season vs Warm Season</a> to understand why the two signals are not interchangeable.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

